name: server.R
content:
library(ggplot2)
library(plotly)
library(dplyr) 
library(shiny)  

source("utils.R")
source("utilsSim.R")

liver = read.csv("merged_liver.csv")
liver = subset(liver, RateConstants < 1)

muscle = read.csv("merged_muscle.csv")
muscle = subset(muscle, RateConstants < 1)

# Define server logic required to draw a histogram
server <- function(input, output) {
  inputdata <- reactive({
    dict <- data.frame(
      key = c("tissue", "time", "terms"),
      value = c(input$tissue, input$time, input$terms)
    )
    
    output <- dict
  })
  processedData <- reactive({
    temp = (inputdata())
    
    
    data = data.frame()
    if (temp$value[temp$key == "tissue"] == "Liver")
      data = liver
    else
      data = muscle
    
    res = as.data.frame(getnewEstimation(as.numeric(temp$value[temp$key == "time"]), as.numeric(temp$value[temp$key == "terms"]), data))
    
    output <- res
  })
  
  output$status <- renderText(if (input$submit > 0) {
    temp = isolate(inputdata())
    
    
    return (paste(c(paste(
      c("Tissue: ", temp$value[temp$key == "tissue"])
    ), paste(
      c(" Days: ", temp$value[temp$key == "time"])
    ), paste(
      c(" Terms: ", temp$value[temp$key == "terms"])
    ))
    , sep = ","))
  }
  else{
    return ("Server is ready for calculation.")
  })
  
  
  output$scatterplot <- renderPlotly({
    if (input$submit > 0) {
      res = isolate(processedData())
      
      # Compute point density
      get_density <- function(x, y, n = 100) {
        dens <- MASS::kde2d(x, y, n = n)
        ix <- findInterval(x, dens$x)
        iy <- findInterval(y, dens$y)
        density <- dens$z[cbind(ix, iy)]
        return(density)
      }
      
      res$density <- get_density(res$d2ome_k, res$new_k)
      
      # res$rd<- 100*abs(res$d2ome_k -res$new_k)/res$d2ome_k
      # res$rd[res$rd > 100] <- 110
      
      # # Create the scatter plot with ggplot
      scatterplot <-  ggplot(res, aes(x = d2ome_k, y = new_k, color = density)) +
        geom_point(size = 2) +
        geom_abline(
          slope = 1,
          intercept = 0,
          color = "red",
          linetype = "dashed",
          linewidth = 1
        ) +
        scale_color_viridis_c(option = "turbo") + # Use a nice color palette for density
        theme_minimal() +
        theme(
          panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
          # Remove major grid lines
          panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
          # Remove minor grid lines
          axis.line = element_line(color = "black"),
          axis.text = element_text(size = 14),
          axis.title = element_text(size = 16, face = "bold")
        ) +
        labs(# title = "Scatter Plot with Density Coloring and Fitted Line",
          x = "k (D2ome)", y = "k (approx.)", color = "Density")
      
      
      
      ggplotly(scatterplot)
      
    }
    
    
  })
  
  
  output$density <- renderPlot({
    if (input$submit > 0) {
      res = isolate(processedData())
      
      # Compute point density
      get_density <- function(x, y, n = 100) {
        dens <- MASS::kde2d(x, y, n = n)
        ix <- findInterval(x, dens$x)
        iy <- findInterval(y, dens$y)
        density <- dens$z[cbind(ix, iy)]
        return(density)
      }
      
      res$density <- get_density(res$d2ome_k, res$new_k)
      
      res$rd <- (res$d2ome_k - res$new_k) / res$d2ome_k
      # res$rd[res$rd > 100] <- 110
      temp_title = paste("mean: ",
                         sprintf("%.3f", mean(res$rd)),
                         "SD: ",
                         sprintf("%.3f", sd(res$rd)) ,
                         sep = " ")
      
      # print((temp_title))
      
      # # Create the scatter plot with ggplot
      ggplot(res, aes(x = rd)) +
        # geom_point(size = 2) +
        geom_histogram(
          aes(y = after_stat(density)),
          fill = "lightblue",
          color = "darkblue",
          bins = 30,
          alpha = 0.6
        ) +  # Histogram
        geom_density(fill = "blue",
                     alpha = 0.3,
                     color = "red") +  # Density plot
        scale_color_viridis_c(option = "turbo") + # Use a nice color palette for density
        
        theme_minimal() +
        theme(
          panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
          panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
          axis.line = element_line(color = "black"),
          axis.text = element_text(size = 14),
          axis.title = element_text(size = 16, face = "bold"),
          
        ) +
        labs(y = "Density", x = "Relative difference") +
        # ggtitle(temp_title)+
        annotate(
          "text",
          x = Inf,
          # Automatically positions the text at the maximum x value
          y = Inf,
          # Automatically positions the text at the maximum y value
          label = temp_title,
          hjust = 1,
          # Align text to the left horizontally
          vjust = 1,
          # Align text to the top vertically
          size = 5,
          # Text size
          color = "blue"  # Text color
        )
      
      
    }
    
  })
  
  inputdataSim <- reactive({
    dict <- data.frame(
      key = c("bwe", "time", "peptide", "neh"),
      value = c(
        input$bwe,
        input$maxTime,
        input$peptide,
        getNeh(input$peptide)
      )
    )
    
    output <- dict
  })
  
  
  output$simstatus <- renderText(if (input$runsim > 0) {
    temp = isolate(inputdataSim())
    
    
    return (paste(c(paste(
      c("Peptide: ", temp$value[temp$key == "peptide"], "(NEH", (temp$value[temp$key == "neh"]), ")")
    ), paste(
      c(" Max. Days: ", temp$value[temp$key == "time"])
    ), paste(
      c(" BWE: ", temp$value[temp$key == "bwe"])
    ))
    , sep = ","))
  }
  else{
    return ("Server is ready for calculation.")
  })
  
  simulateProcessResult <- reactive({
    temp_input = (inputdataSim())
    
    temp_res = getSimulationResult(
      as.numeric(temp_input$value[temp_input$key == "neh"]),
      as.numeric(temp_input$value[temp_input$key == "bwe"]),
      as.numeric(temp_input$value[temp_input$key == "time"])
    )
    
    
    # p1 = temp_res %>% filter(rd < 0.01)
    # p1 = as.data.frame(p1 %>% group_by(time) %>% summarise("k" = max(k), group = "≤ 1%"))
    #
    # p5 = temp_res %>% filter(rd < 0.05)
    # p5 = as.data.frame(p5 %>% group_by(time) %>% summarise("k" = max(k), group = "≤ 5%"))
    #
    # p10 = temp_res %>% filter(rd < 0.10)
    # p10 = as.data.frame(p10 %>% group_by(time) %>% summarise("k" = max(k), group = "≤ 10%"))
    #
    # # print(c("temp_res"=temp_res,"p1"=p1,"p5"=p5,"p10"=p10))
    #
    # output <- c(
    #   "temp_res" = temp_res,
    #   "p1" = p1,
    #   "p5" = p5,
    #   "p10" = p10
    # )
    
    output <- temp_res
  })
  
  output$simplot <- renderPlotly(if (input$runsim > 0) {
    temp_res = isolate(simulateProcessResult())
    
    # print("temp_res--->")
    
    p1 = temp_res %>% filter(rd < 0.01)
    p1 = p1 %>% group_by(time) %>% summarise("k" = max(k), group = "≤ 1%")
    
    p5 = temp_res %>% filter(rd < 0.05)
    p5 = p5 %>% group_by(time) %>% summarise("k" = max(k), group = "≤ 5%")
    
    p10 = temp_res %>% filter(rd < 0.10)
    p10 = p10 %>% group_by(time) %>% summarise("k" = max(k), group = "≤ 10%")
    
    
    
    temp_plot = ggplot() +
      # geom_point(alpha = 0.5) +
      geom_tile(data = temp_res, aes(x = time, y = k, fill = rd))  +  # Basic heatmap
      geom_line(data = p1,
                aes(x = time, y = k, color = group),
                linewidth = 0.5) +
      geom_line(data = p5,
                aes(x = time, y = k, color = group),
                linewidth = 0.5) +
      geom_line(data = p10,
                aes(x = time, y = k, color = group),
                linewidth = 0.5) +
      
      # scale_color_viridis_c(option = "plasma") + # Use a nice color palette for density
      scale_fill_viridis_c(option = "mako") +
      theme_minimal() +
      theme(
        panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
        axis.line = element_line(color = "black"),
        axis.text = element_text(size = 14),
        axis.title = element_text(size = 16, face = "bold"),
        
      ) +
      labs(y = "k", x = "Labeling duration")
    
    
    
    
    ggplotly(temp_plot)
  })
  
  output$simdatatable <- renderTable ({
    if (input$runsim > 0) {
      temp_res = isolate(simulateProcessResult())
      
      p1 = temp_res %>% filter(rd < 0.01)
      p1 = p1 %>% group_by(time) %>% summarise("k" = max(k), group = "≤ 1%")
      
      p5 = temp_res %>% filter(rd < 0.05)
      p5 = p5 %>% group_by(time) %>% summarise("k" = max(k), group = "≤ 5%")
      
      p10 = temp_res %>% filter(rd < 0.10)
      p10 = p10 %>% group_by(time) %>% summarise("k" = max(k), group = "≤ 10%")
      
      temp_data = data.frame(p1$time, p1$k, p5$k, p10$k)
      temp_data %>%
        rename(
          "Labeling Duration" = "p1.time",
          " k (RD ≤ 1%)" = "p1.k",
          "k (RD ≤ 5%)" = "p5.k",
          "k (RD ≤ 10%)" = "p10.k"
        )
      
      
      
    }
  })
  
}

                        max = 50,
                        value = 6

                      actionButton("submit", "Submit", class = "btn btn-danger")

                    mainPanel(
                      verbatimTextOutput("simstatus"),
                      # plotlyOutput("simplot"),

                      # tableOutput("simdatatable")
                      
                      # Output: A tabset that combines three panels ----
                      navset_tab(
                        # title = "Visualizations",
                        # Panel with plot ----
                        nav_panel("Plot", plotlyOutput("simplot")),

                        nav_panel("Summary", tableOutput("simdatatable")),
                        
                        # # Panel with table ----
                        # nav_panel("Table", tableOutput("table"))
                      )
                    )
                  ))
                ))

name: utils.R
content:
# Constants
pw <- 0.046
ph <- 1.5574e-4

# Function to compute I0_t
get_I0_t <- function(I0_0, I0_asymp, k, t) {
  return(I0_asymp + (I0_0 - I0_asymp) * exp(-k * t))
}

# Function to compute I0_asymp
get_I0_asymp <- function(I0_0, neh) {
  return(I0_0 * ((1 - pw / (1 - ph))^neh))
}

# Function to calculate all errors
get_all_error <- function(I0_0, I0_asymp, k, t, I0_t, numberofTerms) {
  if (is.na(I0_t)) {
    I0_t <- get_I0_t(I0_0, I0_asymp, k, t)
  }
  
  new_kt <- get_kt(I0_0, I0_t, I0_asymp)
  
  if (numberofTerms > 1) {
    new_kt <- new_kt + estimatedError(I0_0, I0_t, I0_asymp, numberofTerms)
  }
  
  new_k <- new_kt / t
  
  new_k_error <- 100 * (k - new_k) / k
  
  new_I0_t <- get_I0_t(I0_0, I0_asymp, new_k, t)
  
  return(c(
    new_k = new_k,
    new_k_error = new_k_error,
    I0_t_error = 100 * (I0_t - new_I0_t) / I0_t
  ))
}

# Function to compute kt
get_kt <- function(I0_0, I0_t, I0_asymp) {
  temp_res = ((I0_0 - I0_t) / (I0_0 - I0_asymp))
  return(temp_res)
}

# Function to estimate error
estimatedError <- function(I0_0, I0_t, I0_asymp, numberofTerms) {
  base <- (I0_0 - I0_t) / (I0_0 - I0_asymp)
  
  res <- 0
  
  for (i in 2:numberofTerms) {
    res <- res + (base^i) / i
  }
  
  return(res)
}


getnewEstimation <- function(time, numberofterms, merged) {
  # Constants
  pw <- 0.046
  ph <- 1.5574e-4
  alltime <- c(0 , 1 , 2 , 3 , 6 , 7 , 9 , 13, 16, 21, 24)
  
  # Get the corresponding time
  # time <- exp_time[time_index]
  time_index = which(alltime == time) - 1
  print(c("time", time, time_index, "terms", numberofterms))
  
  res <- list()  # Initialize a list to store results
  
  # Iterate over rows in the data frame
  for (index in 1:nrow(merged)) {
    suffix <- paste0(".", time_index)
    
    # Skip if the 'I0' value is missing or empty
    if (merged[index, paste0("I0", suffix)] == " " ||
        is.na(merged[index, paste0("I0", suffix)])) {
      next
    }
    
    # Calculate the sum of I0 to I5
    m0_sum <- sum(as.numeric(merged[index, paste0("I", 0:5, suffix)]), na.rm = TRUE)
    
    if (m0_sum > 0) {
      # Extract required values
      I0_0 <- as.numeric(merged[index, "M0"]) / 100
      k <- as.numeric(merged[index, "RateConstants"])
      
      # Calculate I0_asymp
      i0_asymp <- I0_0 * ((1 - pw / (1 - ph))^as.numeric(merged[index, "Exchangeable.Hydrogens"]))
      
      
      # Calculate experimental and theoretical i0_t
      i0_t_exp <- as.numeric(merged[index, paste0("I0", suffix)]) / m0_sum
      i0_t_theo <- i0_asymp + (I0_0 - i0_asymp) * exp(-k * time)
      
      temp_error_res <- get_all_error(I0_0, i0_asymp, k, time, i0_t_exp, numberofterms)
      
      
      # Get error estimates
      temp_res <- c(
        I0_0,
        i0_asymp,
        i0_t_exp,
        i0_t_theo,
        k,
        temp_error_res['new_k'],
        temp_error_res['new_k_error'],
        temp_error_res['I0_t_error']
      )
      
      # Append results to the list
      res <- append(res, list(temp_res))
    }
  }
  
  # Convert the list to a data frame
  res <- do.call(rbind, res)
  colnames(res) <- c(
    "M0",
    "I0_asmp",
    "i0_t_exp",
    "i0_t_theo",
    "d2ome_k",
    "new_k",
    "new_k_error",
    "new_erro_i0_t"
  )
  
  return(res)
}

getNeh<-function(peptide) {
  aa_neh = list(
    "A"= 4   ,
    "C"= 1.62, 
    "D"= 1.89, 
    "E"= 3.95, 
    "F"= 0.32, 
    "G"= 2.06, 
    "H"= 2.88, 
    "I"= 1   ,
    "K"= 0.54, 
    "L"= 0.6 ,
    "M"= 1.12,
    "N"= 1.89,
    "P"= 2.59,
    "Q"= 3.95,
    "R"= 3.43,
    "S"= 2.61,
    "T"= 0.2 ,
    "V"= 0.56,
    "W"= 0.08,
    "Y"= 0.42
  )
  
  # print(strsplit(peptide, split = ""))
  
  res=0
  for(aa in strsplit(peptide, "")[[1]]){ 
    res=res+ as.numeric( aa_neh[ as.character(aa)])
  }
  # print(res)
  return (res)
  
}
